{{Infobox football biography |name = Bledar Hajdini |image = |image_size = |caption = |fullname = Bledar Hajdini |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1995|6|19|df=y}} |birth_place = [[Fürstenfeldbruck]], [[Germany]] |height = {{convert|1.91|m|ftin|0|abbr=on}} |position = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]] |currentclub = [[KF Llapi|Llapi]] |clubnumber = 1 |youthyears1 = {{0|0000}}–2013 |youthclubs1 = [[KF Hysi|Hysi]] |youthyears2 = 2013–2015 |youthclubs2 = [[FC Prishtina|Prishtina]] |years1 = 2015–2018 |clubs1 = [[KF Trepça'89|Trepça'89]] |caps1 = 65 |goals1 = 0<!--Appearances and goals are from 2015–16 season--> |years2 = 2018– |clubs2 = [[KF Llapi|Llapi]] |caps2 = 0 |goals2 = 0 |nationalyears1 = 2017– |nationalteam1 = [[Kosovo national football team|Kosovo]] |nationalcaps1 = 1 |nationalgoals1 = 0 |club-update = 1 June 2018 |nationalteam-update = 13 November 2017 }} '''Bledar Hajdini''' (born 19 June 1995) is an [[Kosovo Albanian]] professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for Kosovan club [[KF Llapi|Llapi]] and the [[Kosovo national football team|Kosovo national team]].
==Early life== Hajdini was born in Fürstenfeldbruck, Germany from Kosovo Albanian parents from [[Podujevo]].
==Club career== ===Trepça'89=== In June 2015. Hajdini joined [[Football Superleague of Kosovo]] side [[KF Trepça'89|Trepça'89]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://gazetaolle.com/talenti-nga-vushtrria-nenshkruan-me-trepcen-89/|title=Talenti nga Vushtrria nënshkruan me Trepçën ’89|website=GazetaOlle|language=Albanian|date=20 June 2015}}</ref>
===Llapi=== On 1 June 2018. Hajdini joined [[Football Superleague of Kosovo]] side [[KF Llapi|Llapi]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://futbollikosovar.com/zyrtare-llapi-prezanton-dy-super-perforcimet-e-ardhura-nga-trepca-89-foto/|title=ZYRTARE: Llapi prezanton dy super-përforcimet e ardhura nga Trepça'89 (Foto)|website=Futbolli Kosovar|language=Albanian|date=1 June 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://telegrafi.com/zyrtare-bledar-hajdini-dhe-fiton-hajdari-prezantohen-tek-llapi/|title=Zyrtare: Bledar Hajdini dhe Fiton Hajdari prezantohen tek Llapi|publisher=[[Telegrafi]]|language=Albanian|date=1 June 2018}}</ref>
==International career== On 2 October 2016. Hajdini received a call-up from [[Kosovo national football team|Kosovo]] for a [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification&nbsp;– UEFA Group I|2018 FIFA World Cup qualification]] matches against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] and [[Ukraine national football team|Ukraine]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ffk-kosova.com/en/?p=10919|title=Bunjaki announces the list of players for the matches with Croatia and Ukraine|publisher=[[Football Federation of Kosovo]]|date=2 October 2016}}</ref> On 13 November 2017, he made his debut with Kosovo in a [[Exhibition game|friendly match]] against [[Latvia national football team|Latvia]] after coming on as a substitute at 68th minute in place of [[Samir Ujkani]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.koha.net/sport/57146/fishkellehet-vazhdimisht-ujkani-zevendesohet-nga-hajdini/|title=Fishkëllehet vazhdimisht Ujkani, zëvendësohet nga Hajdini|language=Albanian|publisher=[[Koha Ditore]]|date=13 November 2017}}</ref>
