{{Notability|date=September 2009}} '''Body blading''' (also known as '''buggy rollin'''') is an [[extreme sport]] that involves descending down a slope while wearing a flexible aerodynamic plastic roller suit that has wheels on the feet, knees, torso, and arms. This suit was created by [[Jean-Yves Blondeau]], and he is one of the premier{{Clarify|date=May 2012}} body bladers. Body blading is similar to [[roller blading]], and in fact a body blader often starts out using the rollers on their feet in the same fashion as roller blades in order to gain initial speed, but then the rider generally assumes a position lying on the stomach facing down the hill. A body blader is capable of reaching very high{{Clarify|date=May 2012}} speeds. Maneuverability is achieved by moving the body into various positions to change direction.
