{{notability|date=February 2010}}
'''Boston–Montreal–Boston''' ''(BMB)'' was a 1200&nbsp;km [[Brevet (cycling)|randonnée]] bicycle ride held on an out-and-back course between the vicinity of [[Boston, Massachusetts]] (US) and [[Huntingdon, Quebec]] (Canada). It was held every year from 1988 through 2006 except for [[Paris–Brest–Paris]] years.

BMB was sometimes regarded as the North American equivalent of Paris–Brest–Paris.

It was a noncompetitive endurance bike event.

