{{Use British English|date=December 2017}}
This page covers the seasons from [[1970–71 in Scottish football|1970–71]] to [[1979–80 in Scottish football|1979–80]]<!-- which saw the club win the League and the [[Scottish League Cup|League Cup]], reach three [[Scottish Cup]] finals, and the [[UEFA Champions League|European Cup]] semi-finals and [[UEFA Cup]] Final-->.

==1970&ndash;71==
<!--{{main|Dundee United F.C. season 1970-71}}
-->
The club finished the Division One season in sixth place, missing out on European qualification by one place as rivals [[Dundee F.C.|Dundee]] pipped them by two points. [[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]] knocked United out of the [[Scottish Cup]] in the [[Scottish Cup 1970-71#Fourth round|fourth round]] while the club failed to get past the [[Scottish League Cup|League Cup]] first round. United were knocked out of the [[Inter-Cities Fairs Cup]] in the [[Inter-Cities Fairs Cup 1970&ndash;71#Second round|second round]] by [[Czechoslovakia]]n side [[Sparta Prague|TJ Sparta ČKD Praha]].

