==1971&ndash;72==
<!--{{main|Dundee United F.C. season 1971-72}}
-->
The club finished the Division One season in ninth place, with [[Jim McLean]] beginning a 22-year managerial spell with the club in December 1971, taking over from [[Jerry Kerr]]. [[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]] knocked United out of the Scottish Cup for the second year running, this time in the [[Scottish Cup 1971-72#Third round|third round]], while the club again failed to get past the League Cup first round. In the [[Texaco Cup]], United were beaten 8&ndash;5 on aggregate by eventual winners [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]] in the first round.<ref name="sfh">{{cite web|url=http://www.geocities.com/br1anmccoll/texacocup|title=Texaco Cup 1970-1975|last=McColl|first=Brian|publisher=Scottish Football History|accessdate=2008-06-19|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090806150023/http://geocities.com/br1anmccoll/texacocup|archivedate=2009-08-06}}</ref>

