==1972&ndash;73==
<!--{{main|Dundee United F.C. season 1972-73}}
-->
The club finished the Division One season in seventh place, in [[Jim McLean]]'s first full season since taking over from [[Jerry Kerr]]. [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]] knocked United out of the [[Scottish Cup 1972-73#Third round|Scottish Cup third round]], while the club reached the League Cup second round. In the Texaco Cup, United were again beaten in the first round, this time on [[Penalty shootout (association football)|penalties]] by [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] after a 3&ndash;3 aggregate draw.<ref name="sfh" />

