{{NBA Development League Awards}} The '''Jason Collier Sportsmanship Award''' is an annual [[NBA G League]] award given since the league's [[2001–02 NBDL season|inaugural season]]. The award honors the player who best represents the ideals of character and conduct on and off the court. The league's head coaches determine the award by voting and it is usually presented to the honoree during the G League playoffs.<ref name=major>{{cite web|url=http://bakersfield.dleague.nba.com/news/renaldo-major-receives-nba-d-leagues-jason-collier-sportsmanship-award/|title=RENALDO MAJOR RECEIVES NBA D-LEAGUE’S JASON COLLIER SPORTSMANSHIP AWARD|work=NBA.com|date=April 20, 2015|accessdate=April 16, 2016}}</ref> The award is named after former G League, Houston Rockets and Atlanta Hawks center [[Jason Collier]], who died on October 15, 2005. Collier was a player and person who exemplified the qualities of a faithful teammate, husband, father, son, brother and friend. He was ready to begin his sixth NBA season at the time of his death.<ref name="major" /> [[Billy Thomas (basketball)|Billy Thomas]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/dleague/news/sportsmanship_080411.html|title=Colorado’s Billy Thomas Receives 2007-08 Jason Collier Sportsmanship Award|work=NBA.com|date=April 11, 2008|accessdate=April 16, 2016|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160610060339/http://www.nba.com/dleague/news/sportsmanship_080411.html|archivedate=June 10, 2016|df=}}</ref> and [[Ron Howard (basketball)|Ron Howard]] have both won the award on two occasions.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/dleague/news/fort_wayne_mad_ants_swingman_ron_howard_jason_collier_sportsmanship_award_2013_04_17.html|title=Fort Wayne Mad Ants Swingman Ron Howard Receives 2013 Jason Collier Sportsmanship Award|work=NBA.com|date=April 17, 2013|accessdate=April 16, 2016|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160610060257/http://www.nba.com/dleague/news/fort_wayne_mad_ants_swingman_ron_howard_jason_collier_sportsmanship_award_2013_04_17.html|archivedate=June 10, 2016|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nba.com/dleague/news/ron_howard_wins_sportsmanship_award_2014_04_18.html|title=Fort Wayne's Ron Howard Wins Second Consecutive Jason Collier Sportsmanship Award|work=NBA.com|date=April 18, 2014|accessdate=April 16, 2016|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160610060333/http://www.nba.com/dleague/news/ron_howard_wins_sportsmanship_award_2014_04_18.html|archivedate=June 10, 2016|df=}}</ref>
