'''Malaya Sportivnaya Arena''', also known as '''Malaya Arena''' or '''The Small Arena''',<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldstadiums.com/europe/countries/moldova.shtml |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-05-14 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130623024430/http://www.worldstadiums.com/europe/countries/moldova.shtml |archivedate=2013-06-23 |df= }}</ref> is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Tiraspol]], [[Moldova]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches, and hosts [[FC Sheriff Tiraspol]]'s reserve team games, as well as some [[FC Dinamo Bender]] and [[FC Tiraspol]] matches.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fussballtempel.net/uefa/MOL.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-07-18 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100626001325/http://www.fussballtempel.net/uefa/MOL.html |archivedate=2010-06-26 |df= }}</ref><ref>http://stadiony.net/stadium.php?s=678</ref> 
It is located in the Sheriff Sports Complex, alongside the larger [[Sheriff Stadium]], where the Sheriff Tiraspol senior team plays.  The stadium was built in 2002<ref>http://www.worldstadia.com/stadium/moldova/malaya_sportivnaya_arena/1646.php?PHPSESSID=91b236da035fe1c125fadd4ba3a9b7cc</ref> and has an all-seated capacity of 8,000,<ref>http://www.fc-sheriff.com/eng/club/stadium</ref> making it the [[List of football stadiums in Moldova|third-largest]] stadium in Moldova. The pitch has an artificial [[FieldTurf]] surface, and is surrounded by a six-lane running track.

