{{Football club infobox | clubname = Masafi Al-Janoob SC| image = | fullname = Masafi Al-Janoob Sport Club| founded = {{Start date and age|2005}} | ground = Masafi Al-Janoob stadium| capacity = | owner = [[Ministry of Oil (Iraq)|Ministry of Oil]] | chairman = Adnan Hussein| manager = [[Asaad Abdul Razzak]]| league = [[Iraq Division 1|Iraq Division one]] | season = | position = | website = https://web.facebook.com/%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D8%B1%D9%83%D8%B2-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%B9%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%8A-%D9%84%D9%86%D8%A7%D8%AF%D9%8A-%D9%85%D8%B5%D8%A7%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AC%D9%86%D9%88%D8%A8-828263707197273/?_rdc=1&_rdr | pattern_la1 = _whiteborder | pattern_b1 = _thingreenstripes | pattern_ra1 = _whiteborder | pattern_sh1 = _whitebottom | pattern_so1 = _ | leftarm1 = 008000 | body1 = FFFFFF | rightarm1 = 008000 | shorts1 = 008000 | socks1 = 008000 | pattern_la2 = _mancity1617t | pattern_b2 = _mancity1617t | pattern_ra2 = _mancity1617t | pattern_sh2 = _black_stripes | pattern_so2 = _mancity1617t | leftarm2 = 4600bf | body2 = 4600bf | rightarm2 = 4600bf | shorts2 = 4600bf | socks2 = 4600bf }}
'''Masafi Al-Janoob Sport Club''' ({{lang-ar|'''نادي مصافي الجنوب الرياضي'''}}), is an [[Iraq]]i football team based in [[Shaibah|Al-Shaibah]], [[Basra]], that plays in [[Iraq Division 1|Iraq Division one]].
The team played in the [[Iraqi Premier League]] in [[2009–10 Iraqi Premier League|2009–10 season]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Set the start date of the Iraqi league for the 2009–10 season|url=http://www.alkutnet.com/vb/showthread.php/36862-%D8%AA%D8%AD%D8%AF%D9%8A%D8%AF-%D9%85%D9%88%D8%B9%D8%AF-%D8%A7%D9%86%D8%B7%D9%84%D8%A7%D9%82-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AF%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%85%D9%85%D8%AA%D8%A7%D8%B2-%D8%A8%D9%83%D8%B1%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%82%D8%AF%D9%85-%D9%84%D9%84%D9%85%D9%88%D8%B3%D9%85-2009-2010|website=alkutnet.com|language=Arabic|date=December 3, 2009|last=|first=}}</ref> but relegated to the [[Iraq Division One]] after finished the season in 17th place in the Group Stage.<ref>{{cite web|title=Iraqi League stats for the 2009–10 season|url=http://forum.kooora.com/f.aspx?t=25188537|website=kooora.com|language=Arabic|date=September 6, 2010|last=|first=}}</ref>
==Other games == ===Beach soccer === [[Beach soccer|Masafi Al-Janoob beach soccer team]] won the 2016–17 Iraqi Beach Soccer League title, and transferred trophy of the championship to [[Basra]] for the first time.<ref>{{cite web|title=Masafi Al-Janoob transferred trophy of the Iraqi Beach Soccer League to Basra for the first time|url=http://www.sportgram.net/%D9%85%D8%B5%D8%A7%D9%81%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%AC%D9%86%D9%88%D8%A8-%D9%8A%D9%86%D9%82%D9%84-%D9%84%D9%82%D8%A8-%D8%AF%D9%88%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B4%D8%A7%D8%B7%D8%A6%D9%8A%D8%A9-%D8%A7%D9%84/|website=sportgram.net|language=Arabic|date=August 10, 2017|last=|first=}}</ref>
