{{Infobox football club| | clubname = Sitora Dushanbe | image = | fullname = Sitora Dushanbe | nickname = | founded = {{Start date and age|1990}} | dissolved = {{Start date and age|1997}} | ground = [[Pamir Stadium|Central Republican Stadium]] | capacity = 20,000 | chairman = | manager = | league = [[Tajik League]] | season = [[1997 Tajik League|1997]] | position = 7th | website = | pattern_la1= | pattern_b1=_thinwhitestripes2 | pattern_ra1= | leftarm1=2E8B57 | body1=2E8B57 | rightarm1=2E8B57 | shorts1=FFFFFF | socks1=FFFFFF | pattern_la2= | pattern_b2 = | pattern_ra2= | pattern_so2=_whitehorizontal | leftarm2=FFFFFF | body2=FFFFFF | rightarm2=FFFFFF | shorts2=2E8B57 | socks2=2E8B57 }}
'''Sitora Dushanbe''' ({{lang-tg|Dastai Futboli Sitora|script=Latn}}) was a [[football club]] based in [[Dushanbe]], [[Tajikistan]] between 1990 and 1997.
==History== Sitora Dushanbe were founded in 1990, and went on to win the [[Tajik League]] twice, in [[1993 Tajik League|1993]] and [[1994 Tajik League|1994]]. At the end of the [[1997 Tajik League|1997]] season, Sitora ceased to exist due to financial problems.
